  "text": "As seen in animal studies where different regions of the gut were distended, TLESR appears to be triggered by stretch receptors in various parts of the stomach; particularly in the cardia that are mediated by afferent vagal innervation with inputs into the medullary nuclei, which in turn sends motor outputs through the reflex circuit via vagal and phrenic nerves to elicit prolonged LES relaxation via postganglionic nitrergic neurons [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Given that the mechanism on the TLESR induced by rectal balloon distension in anesthetized dogs are yet to be reported, this was the major aim of this study.",
